Package: dgcmat
Title: Sparse dgCMatrix to faer Bridge via Rust
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Suryansh", "Dey", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "suryansh@example.com")
Description: Extracts the i, p, x slots of an R dgCMatrix sparse matrix via
    extendr, wraps them as Rust slices, constructs a faer sparse matrix, and
    returns the degree vector (row sums of absolute values) to R using
    extendr's Integers type to avoid an unnecessary allocation.
    Demonstrates the dgCMatrix -> faer FFI pattern for the hyperSpec GSoC
    hard test.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
SystemRequirements: Cargo (Rust's package manager), rustc
Imports:
    Matrix
